dimensions.description: The country of the user, specified as a three-letter ISO 3166-1 alpha-3 country code.
The device type of the user. Supported values are: DESKTOP, MOBILE, and TABLET.

The canonical URL of the page. In aggregated-by-property reports, this is the canonical URL of the page that received the impressions and clicks. In aggregated-by-page reports, this is the canonical URL of the page itself.
The query string that the user entered into Google Search.
The search appearance type. This can include values like 'AMP_BLUE_LINK', 'RICHCARD', 'FEATURED_SNIPPET', etc. A single impression can have multiple search appearances.
The date of the user's query, in YYYY-MM-DD format.
